        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer508638405" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3872842737118465655"><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68333.Beggars_in_Spain__Sleepless___1_' title='Beggars in Spain (Sleepless, #1) by Nancy Kress' rel='nofollow noopener'>Beggars in Spain</a> is exactly the kind of science fiction I love. It&apos;s about people and society and the impact of scientific breakthroughs. It explores the big questions of humanity, justice and prejudice. It did run a bit longer than it should have, but the ending was satisfying. The best thing about this novel is that it&apos;s a stand-alone. That&apos;s becoming so rare in SF&amp;F that it&apos;s very refreshing.</span>
  <span id="freeText3872842737118465655" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68333.Beggars_in_Spain__Sleepless___1_" title="Beggars in Spain (Sleepless, #1) by Nancy Kress" rel="nofollow noopener">Beggars in Spain</a> is exactly the kind of science fiction I love. It's about people and society and the impact of scientific breakthroughs. It explores the big questions of humanity, justice and prejudice. It did run a bit longer than it should have, but the ending was satisfying. The best thing about this novel is that it's a stand-alone. That's becoming so rare in SF&amp;F that it's very refreshing.</span>
